<title>UK: Thorn bounces after results.</title>
<headline>Thorn bounces after results.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Thorn Plc bounced on Monday after the group released its nine-month results.</p>
<p>By 1118 GMT, the shares were up 15-1/2p to 202, having lost some 20p last week.  </p>
<p>Thorn said its pre-tax pre-exceptional profits rose eight percent to 123 million stg in the nine-months ended December 31, 1996. But the group said it expected its full-year results to be unchanged from the 170.7 million stg in the year earlier period.</p>
<p>&quot;This is more of a relief factor than anything else,&quot; said one market maker, referring to the advance in the shares.</p>
<p>He said there were concerns that the group would post much weaker profits. --London newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
